<TEXT>
 A union official said Saturday that allegations that <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> ticket agents kept ticket money are part of a `` witch hunt'' by the airline. Four ticket agents at <LOCATION> Kennedy </LOCATION> <LOCATION> International </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> have been charged with stealing about $ 1,400, said <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Cahill </PERSON>, a spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> Port </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, which runs the airport. `` The <ORGANIZATION> Port </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> have determined that $ 48,000 is in fact missing,'' said <PERSON> Cahill </PERSON>. He said <ORGANIZATION> Port </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION> detectives are investigating the four agents and and possibly others in the disappearance of the $ 48,000. <PERSON> Cahill </PERSON> had previously indicated that the four arrested were charged with stealing the total $ 48,000, but he said Saturday he was mistaken. The four agents were charged Friday with falsifying records and larceny for allegedly selling one-way tickets and keeping the cash instead of putting the money in the register, <PERSON> Cahill </PERSON> said. One of the agents, <PERSON> Cathy </PERSON> <PERSON> Alam </PERSON>, is charged with taking just $ 38, <PERSON> Cahill </PERSON> said. An official of the union that represents the agents blasted the charges, calling it part of a scheme by <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> to get rid of some union employees. `` I think this is just a witch hunt,'' said <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Miranda </PERSON>, vice president of Local 732 of the airline division of the <ORGANIZATION> Teamsters </ORGANIZATION>. `` I do n't think these people were involved in a sophisticated scam involving that amount of money,'' <PERSON> Miranda </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Cahill </PERSON> said $ 48,000 is missing in receipts for August and September and that <LOCATION> Port </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Authority </LOCATION> detectives believe ticket agents may have been keeping cash payments for about a year. The investigation, conducted at the request of the airline, will continue and more arrests are expected, <PERSON> Cahill </PERSON> said. A <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> spokesman did n't immediately respond to a telephone request for comment.
