elf. Since he could not stop the meetings, <PERSON> Hawkins </PERSON> said he worked for months before he got the Education Department to agree to allow other education reform programs to be discussed and opponents of `` choice'' to participate. <PERSON> Hawkins </PERSON> also received an invitation to attend but it was uncertain whether he would. Reps. <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Rangel </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.Y. </LOCATION>, and <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Bartlett </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-Texas </LOCATION>, are expected to attend, along with participants from <LOCATION> Maine </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Vermont </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Connecticut </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Rhode </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Maryland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> District </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Columbia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Puerto </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rico </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virgin </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Islands </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Cavazos </PERSON> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Kean </PERSON> will address the meeting. The most controversial form of school choice is allowing parents to send their child to a school outside their school district. But other initiatives include magnet schools that specialize in certain subjects, alternative programs and teacher-initiated schools. So far this year, <LOCATION> Arkansas </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> Nebraska </LOCATION> have joined <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION>, whose open enrollment plan went into effe