<HEAD>Alcoa Profit Down 23 Percent, Sales Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Aluminum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> reported a 23 percent decline in profit in the third quarter, though its sales increased. <ORGANIZATION> Alcoa </ORGANIZATION> said Friday it earned $ 219 million, or $ 2.46 a share, compared with $ 226.3 million, or $ 2.56 a share, posted in the third quarter of 1988. Sales totaled $ 2.8 billion in the third quarter, up 11 percent from the $ 2.6 billion in the third quarter of last year. The company said its third-quarter profit included unfavorable foreign currency adjustments of $ 15.3 million, or 17 cents a share. For the first nine months of 1989, <ORGANIZATION> Alcoa </ORGANIZATION> earned $ 780.2 million, or $ 8.79 a share, compared with $ 642.7 million, or $ 7.27 a share, in the 1988 period. Year-to-date revenues totaled $ 8.2 billion, up 15 percent from $ 7.1 billion in 1988.
